{"word":"κυνηγετέω","slug":"κυνηγετέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κυνηγετέω</b></el> <el>(κῠνηγετέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κυνηγέτης'><el>κυνηγέτης</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to hunt</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to persecute, harass</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to quest about</i>, like a hound, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}